1.20
log
@move a few links from http:// to https://
@
text
@<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>OpenNTPD: Manual Pages</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="description" content="OpenNTPD Manual Pages">
<meta name="copyright" content="This document copyright 1999-2016 by OpenBSD.">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="openbsd.css">
<link rel="canonical" href="http://www.openntpd.org/manual.html">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#23238E">

<h2>
<a href="index.html">
<font color="#0000ff"><i>Open</i></font><font color="#000084">NTPD</font></a>
<font color="#e00000">Manual Pages</font>
</h2>
<hr>
<p>

Web manual pages are available from
<a href="https://www.openbsd.org/">OpenBSD</a>.
These manual pages reflect the latest development release of OpenNTPD.<p>

<ul>
<li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/ntpd">ntpd</a>
     - Network Time Protocol daemon
<li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/ntpctl">ntpctl</a>
     - Network Time Protocol query program
<li><a href="https://man.openbsd.org/ntpd.conf">ntpd.conf</a>
     - Network Time Protocol daemon configuration file
</ul>

The NTP protocol implemented in OpenNTPD is described in
<a href="https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc1305.txt">RFC 1305</a> and
<a href="https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc5905.txt">RFC 5905</a>.
<p>

A reference implementation and other documentation of the NTP protocol is available from <a href="http://www.ntp.org/">ntp.org</a>.

</body>
</html>
@


